item.description:
This tutorial was tested on Ubuntu 20.10, but it should work too on other versions or distributions. You'll have to install packages manually if you don't have apt.
Install VS Code via a way described in the offical VS Code docs Open VS Code and install the ms-vscode.cpptools and ms-vscode.cmake-tools extensions Press Ctrl + Shift+ P and type &quot;preferences: Open Settings (JSON)&quot;
Hit Enter or click the first result and add the following text: 1 2 3 4 5 6 { &#34;cmake.
